    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>Pizzapocalypse is a short game made in twelve weeks by second-year university students.</strong></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>The Story</strong></h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >It feels like the world has forgotten about the joys of authentic, handmade pizza since the oppressive Pizza Corps moved into town with their &quot;cheap and efficient&quot; pizza-in-a-can... but one pizza chef is determined to deliver rich, traditional Italian cuisine. </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3224960/extras/c731284ea2ddc34795cc8c746651946d.poster.avif?t=1768734220\" width=326 height=182 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3224960/extras/c731284ea2ddc34795cc8c746651946d.webm?t=1768734220\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3224960/extras/c731284ea2ddc34795cc8c746651946d.mp4?t=1768734220\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span></p><h2 class=\"bb_tag\" ><strong>Gameplay</strong></h2><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Pizzapocalypse is a cartoony 3D platformer for all skill levels! As a chef, use your pizza to dash and bounce your way across rooftops, and fight robot minions as you traverse a corporation-ridden town to make a delivery to your loyal customers!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Take your time exploring every corner of the beautiful town, and collecting toppings to get the highest score possible!<i> Or</i> master your toolkit to get the fastest time, and attempt to complete bonus challenges. All play styles and skill levels can enjoy Pizzapocalypse!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >The game takes place in one level. Explore the three beautiful and distinct areas, each with multiple paths to uncover, and their own unique gameplay challenges and aesthetic!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ></p>",
